description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northern Devon Healthcare (NDHT) is currently recruiting for a Band 4 Emergency Preparedness Resilience &amp; Response (EPRR) Administration Officer to support the Emergency planning function.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This exciting role will form part of the team that lead an effective and resilient response to the Coronavirus pandemic, Winter pressures and EU Exit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for applicants who are confident, with a team focus but who also have the ability to be self-directing and work independently. You should possess excellent organisational skills as you will be required to prepare the administration process for the incident response.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should have excellent communication skills both written and verbal and possess the necessary qualities to adapt to an ever changing environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is 37.5 hours per week flexing between 7.5 and 12 hour days dependant on the incident response.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note this post is offered at Band 4 Subject to Band Matching.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 15th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
